Vivids to Lived In Color 💕

Behind the Scenes of Model Prep for our New Collect 💋

Started with a Fresh Razor 🪒 Haircut 💇🏽‍♀️ 

Color 🎨 

Step 1: Zigzag Teasie-Lights using @oligopro Cool Blonde & @olaplex 

Step 2: Tint Base back to natural in between highlights with @oligopro Calura Gloss 6N & 7AI 

Step 3: Marry Foils 

*leave out previously lightened ends during the Initial Foil application and then pull through lightener open air during the final processing time to gently lift out old vivids without damage ✅

Step 4: ColorMelt with @schwarzkopfusa TBH 
Root - 5-06 1:1:1 6vol
Mids-Ends 8-64 & 8-04 1:1:1 13vol 
Both mixed with Tone Softener 

Step 5: Treatment @k18hair 

* See Blowdry Tutorial in Previous IGTV featuring @ashleenormanhair Styling Products 

#LockStitchFoilayage 

Tools ⚒️ ANH XXL Board & @styletekbeauty Foils 

Makeup 💄 @muyvette

node.text:
Featuring @ashleenormanhair Styling Products 🙌

* available on website- link in profile 
* available to Licensed Hairstylist for Retail- DM for the Wholesale Link 😘🙏💕

Step 1: Spray ANH “Thick and Fresh” thoroughly section by section root to ends in clean towel dried hair 

Step 2: Section the Front from the back from where the Top of Head rounds forward to the front of the Ears 

Step 3: Pre-Dry focusing on the Root Direction - flat wrap the roots opposite to natural fall to create Volume using the @dysonhairpro Super Sonic Pro

Step 4: Section in 3 large Cirlces - starting in the Hairline front to back

Step 5: Flat Brush “C” Shapes into the Hair by over-directing the hair forward and then back using a @behairfulbrush 

Notes 📝 

* direct the nozzle of the blow dryer down the cuticle layer not straight at the hair using the face of the boar hair brush to smooth and create shine ✨ 

* Never touch the nozzle to the brush - if the natural boar hair bristles of the brush become burnt 🥵 then what do you think is happening to the clients hair? 

Step 6: Spray ANH “Roll in the Hay” Texture Spray thoroughly section by section directed at the roots to soak up oils and add volume 

Step 7: Scrunch in ANH “Oh Behave Cream” at the Mids-ends to add separations and definition 

💥 Stay Tuned for Color Video

But it was so worth the sleep deprivation and annoying everyone sitting around me. I didn’t really have a full idea of what it would mean to me until we won 🥇 

Congratulations @colorbycares @muyvette 🍾 

Love you both so much 😭🙇🏼‍♀️🙏💕

Would you believe me if I told you this was only 42 Foils that can be applied in 1 Hour ?!? 

Foilayage can be a frustratingly long technique and can easily take well over 100 foils and up to 3 hours to apply. I know, I’ve been there 😪

Over-foiling and ending up with a Rootie Platinum is hard not to do. 

Foilayage is supposed to be Balayage inside of Foils for the same visual placement with a lighter lift. If you think about it, we paint open-air on large triangles and can therefore apply a Balayage in about an hour.

I had the idea 💡 of breaking the Round Headshape into inter-locking Triangles, like a Geodesic Dome, and applying 2 Foils per Triangle 📐 One foil to replicate the surface painting and One Foil to replicate the Ombre tip out 🤯

#GeodesicFoilayage 

It’s surprisingly high impact with minimal foils! All the brightness is on the top surface and through the ends and all the depth is underneath for internal dimension 🤓

ColorMelt @schwarzkopfusa TBH

Featuring @ashleenormanhair Styling Products 🙌

* available on website- link in profile 
* available to Licensed Hairstylist for Retail- DM for the Wholesale Link 😘🙏💕

Step 1: Spray ANH “Thick and Fresh” thoroughly section by section root to ends in clean towel dried hair 

Step 2: Section the Front from the back from where the Top of Head rounds forward to the front of the Ears 

Step 3: Pre-Dry focusing on the Root Direction - flat wrap the roots opposite to natural fall to create Volume using the @dysonhairpro Super Sonic Pro

Step 4: Section in 3 large Cirlces - starting in the Hairline front to back

Step 5: Flat Brush “C” Shapes into the Hair by over-directing the hair forward and then back using a @behairfulbrush 

Notes 📝 

* direct the nozzle of the blow dryer down the cuticle layer not straight at the hair using the face of the boar hair brush to smooth and create shine ✨ 

* Never touch the nozzle to the brush - if the natural boar hair bristles of the brush become burnt 🥵 then what do you think is happening to the clients hair? 

Step 6: Spray ANH “Roll in the Hay” Texture Spray thoroughly section by section directed at the roots to soak up oils and add volume 

Step 7: Scrunch in ANH “Oh Behave Cream” at the Mids-ends to add separations and definition 

💥 Stay Tuned for Color Video

We Won @oneshothairawards Collaboration Shot 🏆 

Apparently I was bouncing in my chair and inappropriately clapping  all night 👏😅🙈

I flew from teaching Bilingual classes in Puerto Rico 🇵🇷 to my cousins wedding Washington State to the @behindthechair_com Awards in Austin, Texas in 2 days. I was delirious, we did eat dinner, and our category was the last to be announced at 11:30pm. 

But it was so worth the sleep deprivation and annoying everyone sitting around me. I didn’t really have a full idea of what it would mean to me until we won 🥇 

Congratulations @colorbycares @muyvette 🍾 

Love you both so much 😭🙇🏼‍♀️🙏💕

node.text:
It’s hard to Post about Beauty with so much Ugliness in the World 😭

With the privilege of Freedom I’m living one of the best weeks of my life but I can’t ignore the horrors going on in Afghanistan 🇦🇫💔 

As a Christian, Woman, Mother, Entrepreneur, American - I realize everything I am, have, and stand for would be under attack if I were there. I just can’t imagine it…

All I can think to do is Pray and not stay Silent 🙏
